To change the AMI of the EC2 instance to Ubuntu 16.04, you can update the `ami` variable in the `aws_instance` block to the appropriate AMI ID for Ubuntu 16.04 in the desired region. 

```
resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  ami           = "ami-0453550cbf7bca8c3"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}
```
Please note that the AMI id  `ami-0453550cbf7bca8c3` is for Ubuntu 16.04 in `us-west-2` region. You may have to find the correct AMI id for the region you are using.
